        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 25 at 3:54PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 354 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lake Fenton, or near Grand Blanc, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Atlas, Swartz Creek, Burton, Lake Fenton, Rankin, Grand Blanc,
Davison, Gaines, Goodrich, Linden, and Flint.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
